  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Attached is a .zip with screenshots taken on Windows 7 with clear type enabled.
To have something to compare to, I tried Mozilla's Fira Sans and changed the
body font size to 10pt to better match Tuffy. I also took a screenshot of the
footer, where I changed the background to a flat color. I hope you can evaluate
the situation based on the screenshots. IMO Tuffy doesn't look so bad, but I
guess Fira Sans looks cleaner.

Note that the font in the tweet stream (Gotham Narrow) comes from Twitter.

Fira Sans can be found here:
<a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/styleguide/products/firefox-os/typeface/">http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/styleguide/products/firefox-os/typeface/</a></pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
